<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/vram/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://huggingface.co/spaces/NyxKrage/LLM-Model-VRAM-Calculator"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "LLM VRAM Calculator" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/vram> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The memory available to the GPU for storing model weights and KV cache. Discrete GPUs have dedicated VRAM (typically 8-48GB). Unified memory architectures (Apple Silicon, AMD Strix Halo) share system RAM between CPU and GPU — giving access to 64-128GB+ without PCIe transfer bottlenecks. This is the single most important spec for local LLMs: it determines the largest model you can run." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "VRAM / Unified Memory" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "vram" ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf> ;
