<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/transformer/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://arxiv.org/abs/1706.03762"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Attention Is All You Need (paper)" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/transformer> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The neural network architecture behind all modern LLMs, introduced in the 2017 'Attention Is All You Need' paper. Key innovation: self-attention lets every token attend to every other token, enabling the model to capture long-range dependencies. The architecture consists of stacked layers, each with multi-head attention and feed-forward networks. Model size is measured in parameters — the learnable weights in these layers." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Transformer Architecture" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "transformer" ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf> ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> , <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/tool-calling> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/tool-calling/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/tool-calling/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/tool-use"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Anthropic Tool Use Guide" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/tool-calling> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The ability of an LLM to invoke external tools (read files, run commands, search code) during a conversation. Critical for coding assistants like Claude Code. The model outputs structured JSON describing which function to call and with what arguments. Not all local models support it reliably — tool calling requires strong instruction following and correct JSON generation. Qwen3-Coder-Next and Devstral 2 have the best local tool calling support." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Tool Calling / Function Calling" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "tool-calling" ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf> ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> , <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
