<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/strix-halo/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.amd.com/en/products/processors/laptop/ryzen/ai-max-series.html"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "AMD Product Page" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/strix-halo> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "AMD Ryzen AI Max+ 395 APU with 16 Zen 5 cores, 40 RDNA 3.5 CUs (Radeon 8060S iGPU), and XDNA 2 NPU at 50 TOPS. Supports up to 128GB LPDDR5X-8000 unified memory at ~215 GB/s. The unified memory architecture means GPU and CPU share the same pool — models loaded in RAM are directly accessible by GPU compute units, enabling 70B+ parameter models that discrete GPUs cannot fit." ;
