<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/quantization/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://huggingface.co/docs/optimum/en/concept_guides/quantization"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "HuggingFace Quantization Guide" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/quantization> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The process of reducing the precision of model weights from high-precision (FP16/FP32) to lower-precision (INT8, INT4, FP8, FP4). This shrinks memory usage and speeds up inference at the cost of some quality. Modern quantization methods (GGUF K-quants, AWQ, GPTQ) lose remarkably little quality — a 4-bit model typically retains 90-95% of the full-precision quality. The key tradeoff: bits per weight vs quality vs speed." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Quantization" ;
