<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/parameters> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The learnable weights in a neural network. A '70B model' has 70 billion parameters. Each parameter is typically stored as a 16-bit floating point number (2 bytes), so a 70B model needs ~140GB in full precision. Quantization reduces bits per parameter (e.g., 4-bit = 0.5 bytes), cutting memory requirements dramatically: that 70B model drops to ~42GB at 4-bit." ;
