<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/npu/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.qualcomm.com/news/onq/2024/07/what-is-an-npu-and-what-does-it-mean-for-the-ai-pc"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "What is an NPU?" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/npu> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Dedicated AI accelerator built into modern CPUs/SoCs. Optimized for neural network operations at low power. AMD's XDNA 2 in Strix Halo provides 50 TOPS. NPUs are efficient for smaller models and prompt prefill, but lack the memory bandwidth of GPUs for large-model token generation. Still early days for LLM inference on NPUs — Lemonade and FastFlowLM are pioneering this space." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
