<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/moe/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://huggingface.co/blog/moe"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "HuggingFace MoE Guide" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/moe> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "An architecture where only a subset of parameters (experts) are active for each token. Mixtral 8x22B has 141B total but only 39B active per token; Qwen3-Coder-Next has 80B total but only 3B active. MoE models give better quality per compute, but ALL parameters must fit in memory even though only some are used. Unified memory (like Strix Halo) is ideal — no PCIe bottleneck for accessing the dormant experts." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Mixture of Experts (MoE)" ;
