	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Memory Bandwidth in LLM Inference" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/memory-bandwidth> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The rate at which data can be read from memory, measured in GB/s. This is the bottleneck for token generation (decode phase): each token requires reading all model weights once. A 70B model at 4-bit (42GB) on Strix Halo (~215 GB/s) generates ~5 tok/s (215/42). Discrete GPUs have higher bandwidth (NVIDIA RTX 4090: ~1TB/s) but less memory (24GB). The unified memory tradeoff: more capacity, lower bandwidth." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Memory Bandwidth" ;
