<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/llm> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "A neural network trained on massive text corpora to predict the next token in a sequence. LLMs can generate code, answer questions, reason about problems, and follow instructions. They range from 1B to 1T+ parameters. Running them locally means the model weights and computation stay on your machine — no data leaves, no API costs, no rate limits. The tradeoff is hardware requirements: a 70B model at 16-bit precision needs ~140GB of memory." ;
