<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/kv-cache/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.scaleway.com/en/blog/understanding-kv-cache-the-backbone-of-llm-efficiency/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "KV Cache in LLMs" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/kv-cache> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "During inference, the model stores key and value tensors from its attention layers for all previously processed tokens. This avoids recomputing them for each new token but grows linearly with context length. A 70B model at 128K context can use 20-40GB just for KV cache. KV cache quantization (Q4/Q8 KV in llama.cpp) dramatically reduces this overhead — a key optimization for long-context local inference." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "KV Cache" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "kv-cache" ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf> ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> , <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
