<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/inference/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.databricks.com/glossary/llm-inference"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "LLM Inference Explained" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/inference> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Running a trained model to generate output (as opposed to training it). Local LLM inference has two phases: prefill (processing the input prompt, compute-bound) and decode (generating tokens one by one, memory-bandwidth-bound). Decode speed is measured in tokens per second (tok/s). On consumer hardware, expect 5-30 tok/s depending on model size and quantization." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#concepts> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Inference" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "inference" ;
