	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#format> , <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gguf> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gguf/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gguf/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://ggufloader.github.io/what-is-gguf.html"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GGUF Format Guide" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gguf> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The standard quantization format for llama.cpp and Ollama. Successor to GGML. Supports K-quants (Q2_K through Q8_0), I-quants (IQ1_S through IQ4_XS), and full precision (F16, F32). K-quants offer the best quality-per-bit tradeoff for most use cases. GGUF files are self-contained with model metadata, tokenizer, and weights in a single file." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#quantization> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GGUF" ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "gguf" ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf> ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#format> , <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gemma2-27b> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gemma2-27b/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gemma2-27b/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://huggingface.co/google/gemma-2-27b-it"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "HuggingFace" ;
	a <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/local-llm-graph/rdf/node/gemma2-27b> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Google's 27B model. Punches above its weight — competitive with Llama 3.1 70B on some tasks. At Q4_K_M uses ~17GB. Limitation: only 8K context, which is restrictive for code tasks requiring large file context." ;
	<https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#general-models> ;
